<FIRST>r a BC-Opera     03-31 0259</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Opera,0270</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kraus Is Splendid in Met's `Werther'</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: No PMs Planned</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARY CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Tenor <PERSON> Alfredo </PERSON> <PERSON> Kraus </PERSON> brought dignity and elegance to the title role of <PERSON> Massenet </PERSON>'s `` Werther,'' the final opera to enter this season's repertory at the Metropolitan Opera. Some tenors portray <PERSON> Werther </PERSON> as a self-pitying nut case as he pines for his beloved <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION>, who has married another man to fulfill a promise to her dying mother. But in Wednesday's performance <PERSON> Kraus </PERSON> gave him the dignity of a man feeling overwhelming love. Vocally he was lean, elegant, refined, distinguished. <PERSON> Frederica </PERSON> <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Stade </PERSON> as <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION> sang well throughout but rather blandly in the first two acts, as she denied her love for <PERSON> Werther </PERSON> and stuck steadfastly to her husband. In Act 3, with her love churning to the surface as Werther falls into suicidal depression, <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Stade </PERSON> came through with passionate vocalizing. <PERSON> Dawn </PERSON> <PERSON> Upshaw </PERSON> sang <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION>'s sister <PERSON> Sophie </PERSON> in a voice as fresh as spring. It almost seemed to lilt. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Stilwell </PERSON> did well with <PERSON> Albert </PERSON>. All voices were well focused. <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Fournet </PERSON> conducted his first `` Werther'' at the Met, beautifully shaping the music. The present production, last heard at the Met eight years ago, was new in 1971. <PERSON> Rudolf </PERSON> <PERSON> Heinrich </PERSON>'s sets for Acts 1 and 2 are realistic and attractive. After <PERSON> Werther </PERSON>'s mind cracks, set walls meet at odd angles. In the finale scene, his room looks like a coal cellar. `` Werther'' will be heard on the Metropolitan's last Saturday afternoon broadcast. The season ends April 16.
</TEXT>
