> and <PERSON> Cantor </PERSON> <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> <PERSON> Selter </PERSON> are scheduled to lead Passover services in the <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> Choral Synagogue on Friday, and the <ORGANIZATION> Choral </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Synagogue </ORGANIZATION>'s chief rabbi, <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> <PERSON> Shayevich </PERSON>, will be in the pulpit in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. And there are more subtle signs of change. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Stolar </PERSON>, the 28-year-old son of Chicago-born refusenik <PERSON> Abe </PERSON> <PERSON> Stolar </PERSON>, said he and a group of six friends meet daily in the Choral Synagogue to study the Talmud, the writings on Jewish civil and religious law. `` Two to four years ago, you had to be quite careful about where you prayed or studied. You could have an unexpected visit by the militia,'' he said. Still, problems remain. Thousands of Jews are waiting to leave. And anti-Semitism persists: a Soviet newspaper this week accused <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION>'s other synagogue of brainwashing Jewish children into wanting to go to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, and the word `` No!'' was scrawled in English next to a Star of <PERSON> David </PERSON> on an outside wall of the matzoh bakery.
