<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sir <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON>, a former prime minister, died today after a long battle with cancer. He was 80. <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON> died early today at <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Luke </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Sydney </LOCATION> and was cremated in a private service shortly afterward, family members said. <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON> served as prime minister and head of the <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> in 1971-72, and previously headed the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> and Foreign Affairs Department. He became prime minister on March 10, 1971, after <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorton </PERSON> was ousted as prime minister and <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leader in a dispute within the party. But <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON> lost to <PERSON> Gough </PERSON> <PERSON> Whitlam </PERSON> the following year. <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON> entered <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> in 1949. Prime Minister <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Hawke </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> praised <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON>'s service `` Although on opposite sides of the political fence, I found Sir <PERSON> William </PERSON> a generous opponent. He maintained an enormous enthusiasm for and interest in public affairs after his retirement from <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> and was constructive in his discussions on economics and political matters,'' <PERSON> Hawke </PERSON> said in a statement. <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leader <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> said: `` Few parliamentarians in the postwar period could boast a career as rich and diverse as Sir <PERSON> William </PERSON>'s.'' Former Liberal Prime Ministe