<HEAD>March 27, 1984</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Attorney General <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> French </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> asks for a special prosecutor to investigate allegations against <PERSON> Meese </PERSON>, who had recently been nominated to be French's successor. The investigation was prompted by reports that <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> failed to list on his financial disclosure form an interest-free $ 15,000 loan his wife received from <PERSON> Edwin </PERSON> <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>, his wife and son were appointed to federal jobs. The investigation also would look into other transactions, including the loan from <PERSON> McKean </PERSON>.
</TEXT>
