<HEAD>`General Hospital' Celebrates 25 Years on the Air</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The soap opera `` General Hospital'' celebrates its 25th anniversary on Friday showing no signs of ill health in the Nielsen ratings, a recovery that began when it went on location and added such contemporary anti-heroes as <PERSON> Luke </PERSON> and <PERSON> Laura </PERSON>. The show, which began as a straightforward hospital drama on April 1, 1963, was almost dead in the ratings when <PERSON> Gloria </PERSON> <PERSON> Monty </PERSON> took over as executive producer in 1978, infusing the show with contemporary plots and characters. Since 1979, it has been consistently No. 1 in daytime. In 1981, the wedding of shady characters <PERSON> Luke </PERSON> and <PERSON> Laura </PERSON> attracted an audience of nearly 17 million people _ in prime time, the equivalent might be a combination of a Super Bowl and the `` Who Shot J.R.?'' episode of `` <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION>.'' The show was so popular, even <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON> did a guest shot. A popular song was inspired _ `` General Hospi-tale.'' For the first quarter of 1988, `` General Hospital'' tied with <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>' `` The Young and the Restless'' for first place in the daytime Nielsens, with an average rating of 8.6 and 27 share. The rating is a percentage of 88.6 million <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> households with televisions. The share is a percentage of the sets in use. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Beradino </PERSON>, as Dr. <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Harvey </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Emily </PERSON> <PERSON> McLaughlin </PERSON>, as nurse <PERSON> Jessie </PERSON> <PERSON> Brewer </PERSON>, have been with the show since it began. <PERSON> Rachel </PERSON> <PERSON> Ames </PERSON>, who joined the next year as <PERSON> Audrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Hardy </PERSON>, also still appears. Under <PERSON> Monty </PERSON>'s guidance the show was expanded to an hour and took on action-oriented storylines that turned it into a pop phenomenon. `` General Hospit