<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Cher </PERSON> says she enjoyed making the movie `` Moonstruck'' because it gave her a chance to be part of a big, traditional family. In real life, <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>, 40, lives with a 23-year-old acting student and copes with the travails of motherhood. Her 11-year-old son, <PERSON> Elijah </PERSON> <PERSON> Blue </PERSON>, is `` a little superficial,'' and her daughter, 18-year-old Chastity, `` dresses like a bum,'' she complained in an interview with <ORGANIZATION> Film </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Comment </ORGANIZATION> magazine that was reprinted in the April issue of <LOCATION> US </LOCATION>. `` I'm not a cookie-baking mother,'' said <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>, who is up for the Academy Award for best actress for her role in `` Moonstruck.'' `` Well, that's not true. I am a cookie-baking mother, but I'm not a traditional cookie-baking mother.'' Her boyfriend, <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Camilletti </PERSON>, on the other hand, makes bagels _ and <PERSON> Cher </PERSON> said it infuriates her when people `` dismiss him as a bagel maker.'' `` Do I feel insulted when they dismiss everything about him and boil it down to that, without a moment's thought to what kind of a human being he is? Yes. I lived with him when he was a doorman, when he was a bartender. I do n't really care what he is.''
