<HEAD>Bright &amp; Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOMERVILLE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Officials here have hired an outside expert to generate noise in their courtrooms. Court administrator <PERSON> Eugene </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Farkas </PERSON> said Wednesday that some of the courtrooms in the county's new $ 15 million judicial complex are so well designed acoustically that jurors and spectators are privy to even whispered conferences between lawyers and the judge at the bench. `` In the circular courtrooms there is excellent paneling, recess lighting, acoustical tiles and the sound seems to ring the ceiling and come down upon you,'' <PERSON> Farkas </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Noise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Unlimited </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Somerville </LOCATION> is working on the problem. The firm is experimenting with a noise generator that utilizes the sound system in each courtroom to pump in low-level sounds that help mask conversations.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Men like to see women's legs. So what else is new? What's new, according to a poll published Thursday, seems to be that while 36 percent of men say they favor miniskirts on women, and 71 percent say they like skirts at the knee or above, follow-up interviews indicate men generally concede that women have to consider whether showing too much leg is a wise career choice. <PERSON> Greg </PERSON> <PERSON> Parker </PERSON>, of <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, said he likes short skirts because they're `` attractive'' and `` sexy.'' But, the 25-year-old engineer said, `` if you're in a meeting and everyone's dressed conservatively, there's less distraction.'' In The <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Times-CBS telephone poll of 1,654 adults, a quarter of the women questioned said they had worn a skirt above their knees in the past year, while 46 percent of the women said they prefer a length below the knee. The poll was conducted between March 19 and 22. The tepid response of women to the new short styles had already been made apparent at the cash registers to those in the fashion trade, prompting designers to show some longer skirts in their fall collections.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Snoopy pops up in the darndest places, but when the cartoon beagle was found cavorting with a grizzly bear and a laboring miner on the state shield, <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> officials thought some prankster had gone too far. The `` Peanuts'' comic strip canine first surfaced in official circles on the February issue of the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corrections </ORGANIZATION> newsletter. He appeared to have taken the place of the Roman goddess <PERSON> Minerva </PERSON> as she stood on guard, the <LOCATION> Sierra </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> range at her back, a cluster of grapes at her feet. `` Frankly, we first thought it might be the inmates'' up to a prank, said corrections spokesman <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Winkle </PERSON>. `` If I still did n't know anything about it, I would think it was definitely a Snoopy,'' he said. But, no. It was a simple case of bureaucratic thriftiness, according to <PERSON> Curt </PERSON> <PERSON> Soderlund </PERSON>, spokesman for the state <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>. He said a thin line on a printing plate had worn out, creating the appearance of `` something canine.'' It cost $ 50 to fix, he said.
