<SECOND>AM-Blood Pressure Deaths,0540</SECOND>
<HEAD>Drug Cuts High Blood Pressure Related Deaths Almost In Half</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: For release 5:30 p.m. EST.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By PAUL RAEBURN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Science Editor</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 High blood pressure patients given the drug metoprolol had a 48 percent lower death rate than patients given more commonly used drugs, researchers said Thursday. Metoprolol -LRB- pronounced muh-TAH-pro-lawl -RRB- is one of the heart drugs known as beta blockers. The researchers said this is the first study to show that beta blockers can prevent more deaths in people with hypertension than can the widely used diuretics called thiazides. The American <ORGANIZATION> Heart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> estimates that 59 million Americans suffer from high blood pressure, or hypertension. `` We now have scientific proof that if we start with a beta blocker ... we will have a substantial reduction in deaths,'' said the study's principal author, Dr. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Wikstrand </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Gothenburg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Sahlgrenska </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>. Customary practice in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> had been to prescribe diuretics first for high blood pressure and to try beta blockers later if the diuretics were n't working, said Dr. <PERSON> Stevo </PERSON> <PERSON> Julius </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Michigan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Arbor </PERSON>. New recommendations by a committee of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Heart </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Lung </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Blood </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> say that diuretics, beta blockers, or two newer classes of anti-hypertension drugs can serve as the first-line treatment for high blood pressure, said <PERSON> Julius </PERSON>, an advisor to that committee. <PERSON> Julius </PERSON>, who was not part of the study, joined <ORGANIZATION> Wikstrand </ORGANIZATION> at a press conference at <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s Plaza Hotel to discuss the study's findings The press conference was sponsored by metoprolol's developer, the <ORGANIZATION> Astra </ORGANIZATION> pharmaceutical company of <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>, and by <ORGANIZATION> Ciba-Geigy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pharmaceuticals </ORGANIZATION>, which holds the license to market the drug in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> The results of the study will appear Friday in the Journal of the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. Two earlier studies that compared beta blockers and diuretics failed to find any significant difference in the death rate, said Dr. <PERSON> Curt </PERSON> <PERSON> Furberg </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Bowman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gray </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medicine </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Winston-Salem </LOCATION>, <PERSON> N.C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Furberg </PERSON>, who recently wrote a medical journal article reviewing anti-hypertension drugs, called the new study interesting. But, he said in a telephone interview, `` I'm not sure how it's going to be accepted. It's possible we need to test it in a separate study.'' Wikstrand and colleagues at 66 centers in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> monitored 3,234 men given either metoprolol or diuretics for a median period of 4.2 years. The researchers found a 48 percent lower death rate among men given metoprolol than those given diuretics. The drop was mostly due to a reduction in deaths from stroke and coronary heart disease, two complications of high blood pressure, the researchers said. There was no significant effect on other causes of death, suggesting that the drugs are safe, they said. The thiazides make up one class of diuretics, which relieve high blood pressure by stimulating the body to expel fluid, thus lowering the total volume of blood in the bloodstream. Beta blockers block the stimulating action of adrenaline, reducing the rate and the force at which the heart pumps blood through the body _ and reducing high blood pressure.
</TEXT>
