<HEAD>New Award Aimed at Promoting Quality in American Products</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARTIN CRUTSINGER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Directors of a new national award aimed at promoting the quality of <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> products said Thursday they have raised $ 2.2 million to finance the competition and will announce the first winners in November. The <PERSON> Malcolm </PERSON> <PERSON> Baldrige </PERSON> National Quality Award was created by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> in August and named after the late commerce secretary, who was killed last year in a horse riding accident. Officials said Thursday that a maximum of six awards will be given annually _ two each for large manufacturing companies, large service companies and smaller companies engaged in either manufacturing or service. `` Quality is a key weapon in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s arsenal in the international battle for markets,'' <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Verity </PERSON> said in making the announcement. `` This award, which will be <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Nobel Prize for quality, should help recognize the firms that are making a difference when it comes to quality.'' The competition will be supervised by the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standards </ORGANIZATION> in conjunction with a private foundation created by the legislation to raise money for the contest each year Directors of the new foundation are: <PERSON> Sanford </PERSON> <PERSON> N. </PERSON> <PERSON> McDonnell </PERSON>, chairman emeritus of the <ORGANIZATION> McDonnell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Douglas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudiburg </PERSON>, head of <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Power </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGA