<HEAD>White House Announces Financial Moves; Senate Passes Resolution</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: Adds 4 grafs to UPDATE with senators' letter.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By TERENCE HUNT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP White House Correspondent</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The White House announced steps Thursday to encourage American companies to withhold payments from <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> and warned that mandatory action will be considered if the voluntary measures are not sufficient. The action follows the disclosure that some American firms are paying taxes and fees to <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> for doing business there, undercutting the economic sanctions imposed by the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to force the ouster of strongman <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>. Announcing the new action, <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said, `` we are giving <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> companies and persons an incentive and opportunity not to provide financial support to the <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> regime. `` Should these measures prove insufficient, we will review additional legal steps that may be necessary to deny transfer of funds to the <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> regime from <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> companies and persons,'' <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government payments owed the government of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> will be deposited in the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> already is withholding canal fees, toll payments and other funds. <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said withholding taxes for <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> employes in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> and rental payments also will go in the new account. He also said the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> will take part in legal cases by private parties who ow