<BYLINE>By JOHN FLESHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Supporters of slain judicial candidate <PERSON> Julian </PERSON> <PERSON> Pierce </PERSON> asked Gov. <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> on Thursday to convene a special legislative session to allow another minority candidate to seek the post. <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> was noncommittal after the closed meeting in his office. He said he would consult with <PERSON> Pierce </PERSON>'s former opponent, party and legislative leaders and others, and expected to reach a decision next week. <PERSON> Pierce </PERSON>, 42, a Lumbee Indian attorney, was shot to death Saturday at his rural home in racially troubled <LOCATION> Robeson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, where he was running for a newly created <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> judgeship. At first, authorities said the killing looked like a political assassination. But Tuesday they arrested a young Indian man and said a second suspect committed suicide, and attributed <PERSON> Pierce </PERSON>'s killing to a romantic dispute <PERSON> Pierce </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Robeson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> District Attorney <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Freeman </PERSON> <PERSON> Britt </PERSON>, who is white, were slated to meet in the May 3 Democratic primary. Under law, if a candidate dies more than 30 days after filing for a primary has closed, his opponent wins the nomination. In this case, there is no Republican in the race, so <PERSON> Britt </PERSON> would also automatically win the general election in November. Supporters of <PERSON> Pierce </PERSON> asked for a special session to amend the law to let another candidate enter the race. The governor, who planned to meet with <PERSON> Britt </PERSON> on Friday, told reporters: `` I'm going to do my best to try to get input that I need and then take a brief time to think about it very prayfully and come up with the best answer that I can.'' The new <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATI