<HEAD>With AM-Pulitzers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KILEY ARMSTRONG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Tim </PERSON> <PERSON> Weiner </PERSON> blushed happily and climbed on top of a desk Thursday as his colleagues at The <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> Inquirer applauded after he captured the Pulitzer Prize for national reporting. But <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Shales </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> was in shock. `` I'm in a state of slack-jawed dumbfoundedness,'' said <PERSON> Shales </PERSON>, the winner for criticism for his writing on television. `` I'm shocked and delighted and very proud of the paper It's an award that really comes to the paper _ not to me; it's a nice feeling to have brought it to the paper.'' Reporters at the Inquirer, which claimed its 14th prize in 13 years, crowded around the newsroom and applauded when word of <PERSON> Weiner </PERSON>'s prize moved on The Associated Press wire. The recipient, who won for his series on a secret <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> budget used to sponsor defense research and an arms buildup, climbed onto a desk to say, `` I thank you very much.'' He then puffed on a cigar. <PERSON> Weiner </PERSON>, 31, who came to the Inquirer in 1982 from the <ORGANIZATION> Kansas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>, said he feels like he just received a `` $ 10 million check from <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON>. I'm just a very happy guy and very lucky.'' <PERSON> Toni </PERSON> <PERSON> Morrison </PERSON>, winner of the fiction award for `` Beloved,'' said joy was uppermost in her feelings because `` I really was thinking dark and difficult thoughts about what was available to this book in terms of recognition.'' The book became a center of controversy when it did not win two other major literary prizes, and <PERSON> Morrison </PERSON> said she respected the Pulitzer committee for ignoring `` outside matters of speculation and gossip and some slander.'' <ORGANIZATIO