to convict <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, and it's up to each of them to decide what that means. Also, GOP Sen. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> DeLong </PERSON> noted, the governor does not have to be guilty of a crime to be convicted in an impeachment trial; <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> can be removed for malfeasance in office. `` There's more than just the guilt or innocence on the charges,'' <PERSON> DeLong </PERSON> said, adding that he expected senators to be told by the presiding officer that they must `` take action which is in the best interest of <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> ... based on -LRB- <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s -RRB- ability to continue in office.''
