<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market lapsed into a broad decline today in an atmosphere of caution heading into the long Easter-Passover weekend. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 9.95 to 1,968.17 by noontime on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by more than 2 to 1 in the overall tally of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 381 up, 913 down and 488 unchanged. Analysts said traders were reluctant to carry big positions through the weekend, especially with a <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> report coming Friday on the employment situation for March. Both the stock and bond markets will be closed on Friday, and thus will not have a chance to respond to any surprises in the employment data until Monday. In the last set of figures, a much stronger-than-expected increase in nonfarm payroll employment dealt the bond market a sharp setback. Brokers said money managers at investing institutions had pretty much completed maneuvers to ready their portfolios for reports to clients on their performance in the first quarter, which ends with today's trading. Losers among the blue chips included <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION>, down -LCB- at 70 -RCB-; <ORGANIZATION> Merck </ORGANIZATION>, down 1 -LCB- at 156; <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paper </ORGANIZATION>, down 1 at 40 \, and <ORGANIZATION> Procter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gamble </ORGANIZATION>, down -LCB- at 77 <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Richfield </LOCATION> rose 1 -LCB- to 83. The company said its first-quarter earnings are expected to come in above $ 2 a share, against $ 1.31 in the comparable period last year. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks lost .77 to 145.45. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was down .51 at 293.16. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 67.27 million shares at noontime, down from 74.81 million at the same point Wednesday.
